data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":248,"item_id":"msg_05cf62928393161b0069373cd5ab30819689f351e4108b86eb","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"The **Contoso Electronics Whistleblower Policy** ensures a safe and transparent working environment, encouraging employees, contractors, and third parties to report any unethical or illegal activities. Key aspects include:\n\n1. **Definition**: A whistleblower is an individual reporting illegal, unethical actions or violations of company policies.\n2. **Reporting Procedures**: \n   - Contact the Human Resources Department.\n   - Email the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n   - Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n   - Reports can be made anonymously via the Compliance Hotline.\n3. **Details to Include in Reports**: \n   - Time and date of the incident.\n   - Individuals involved.\n   - Description of the incident.\n   - Any supporting evidence.\n4. **Retaliation Prohibition**: Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited and subject to disciplinary action.\n5. **Confidentiality**: The whistleblower's identity will be kept confidential as legally permissible. \n6. **Investigation**: Reports will be promptly and thoroughly investigated.\n\nThis policy is designed to ensure ethical practices and maintain a secure workplace environment.","logprobs":[]}

